Can you try and stay still for me. HE MOANS

02:16.800 --> 02:19.800
I'm just lifting up your visor, OK?

02:19.800 --> 02:22.280
Er, no... I'm a doctor, I just happened to be passing.

02:22.280 --> 02:23.920
He's breathing, alert.

02:23.920 --> 02:25.560
Yes, yes, OK.

02:25.560 --> 02:26.960
Thank you.

02:28.200 --> 02:31.440
You seem fine, but I need you to stay absolutely still.

02:31.440 --> 02:33.560
Partly because of the risk of nerve damage,

02:33.560 --> 02:35.120
also I don't want blood on my shirt

02:35.120 --> 02:38.040
because I've got a really important meeting, is that all right?

02:38.040 --> 02:39.560
HE MURMURS

02:39.560 --> 02:41.000
Sorry?

02:41.000 --> 02:42.240
What?

02:42.240 --> 02:44.160
HE RETCHES

02:44.160 --> 02:45.840
HE COUGHS

02:48.560 --> 02:50.080
Hi.

02:50.080 --> 02:52.240
Jesus! What happened to you?

02:53.440 --> 02:54.640
Traffic.

02:58.080 --> 03:05.120
'This programme contains some strong language and some scenes of a sexual nature.'

03:55.600 --> 03:59.000
My thoughts keep running over the last two years.

03:59.000 --> 04:00.640
Birthdays, holidays.

04:02.520 --> 04:05.640
When we've had sex and I've told him that I love him.

04:07.960 --> 04:10.280
Walking around in the bedroom without any clothes on,

04:10.280 --> 04:12.080
thinking he likes what he sees...

04:14.480 --> 04:16.480
He was lying the whole time.

04:18.480 --> 04:22.760
- Sorry, you're a lawyer, you don't need to hear this. 
- It's fine.

04:26.040 --> 04:29.000
I asked you to bring in details of your finances...

04:29.000 --> 04:31.520
- There. 
- These are just your current account.

04:31.520 --> 04:33.840
Presumably, there are other savings, investments?

04:33.840 --> 04:36.320
- He handles the money, always has done. 
- Why?

04:36.320 --> 04:38.360
He said he was better at it.

04:38.360 --> 04:40.560
So, you don't know your financial situation at all?

04:42.520 --> 04:44.160
No, I suppose...

04:45.440 --> 04:48.240
This project, what's it called?

04:48.240 --> 04:50.800
- Academy Green. 
- And will it pay off?

04:52.320 --> 04:53.920
He says it's doing well.

04:53.920 --> 04:55.440
- He "says"... 
- Sorry.

04:56.560 --> 04:58.640
This is...

04:58.640 --> 05:01.400
No offence, but I'm not interested.

05:01.400 --> 05:05.320
This is really dull. This is not what my life is about. I just...

05:07.640 --> 05:11.040
- I just want to skip to the bit where I move on. 
- In a divorce,

05:11.040 --> 05:13.920
he'll officially take 50% of everything.

05:13.920 --> 05:18.120
- Your salary, your savings, your pension. 
- He cheated. Not me.

05:18.120 --> 05:20.560
Doesn't matter. 50% is the default.

05:20.560 --> 05:23.480
But if you're telling me he has complete control of your finances,

05:23.480 --> 05:25.800
he might already have hidden money away in preparation.

05:25.800 --> 05:29.160
Meaning...you could get even less. Are you happy with that?

05:29.160 --> 05:31.280
- No, of course not. 
- Look.

05:31.280 --> 05:33.680
By not telling him that you know,

05:33.680 --> 05:36.040
you've got an unusual advantage.

05:36.040 --> 05:39.680
You can look into this without him suspecting anything.

05:39.680 --> 05:41.320
So, what do I do?

05:41.320 --> 05:44.040
Depends what you want.

05:45.280 --> 05:48.280
I want my son to stay living in the town where he was born.

05:48.280 --> 05:52.240
I want to keep the life that I chose, the job that I love.

05:53.320 --> 05:54.440
My dignity.

05:55.680 --> 05:57.720
My money and my house.

05:57.720 --> 05:59.560
Good. Then, in the meantime,

05:59.560 --> 06:01.760
find out what he's planning.

06:01.760 --> 06:03.320
How much money he's got.

06:03.320 --> 06:06.000
And while you do that, play the dutiful wife

06:06.000 --> 06:07.720
so he doesn't suspect a thing.

06:17.200 --> 06:19.560
Morning, ladies and gentlemen, thank you for coming.

06:19.560 --> 06:21.240
HE CLEARS THROAT

06:21.240 --> 06:23.360
Highbrook has a proud history.

06:23.360 --> 06:27.520
Generations of children have been educated here, including myself.

06:27.520 --> 06:29.520
Um, then, three years ago,

06:29.520 --> 06:31.560
the building was deemed unsuitable.

06:31.560 --> 06:35.000
The school relocated to a purpose-built facility,

06:35.000 --> 06:38.840
and now, I'm proud that the Academy Green development

06:38.840 --> 06:42.240
will give a new lease of life to this historic site.

06:42.240 --> 06:43.680
MAN: Quite right!

06:43.680 --> 06:46.320
20 luxury flats, right in the heart of town.

06:46.320 --> 06:48.280
APPLAUSE

06:48.280 --> 06:51.720
This isn't just a business opportunity for me,

06:51.720 --> 06:55.600
but a way of protecting the legacy of a building I love.

06:55.600 --> 06:58.960
So, I hope you'll all join me for a glass of champagne...

06:58.960 --> 07:01.080
Um, please take a brochure,

07:01.080 --> 07:04.480
and let's, um... Let's move forward! Let's build! Thank you.

07:04.480 --> 07:06.320
CHUCKLING AND APPLAUSE

07:07.320 --> 07:08.880
- Was that all right? 
- Yes.

07:11.040 --> 07:12.640
HUM OF CONVERSATION

07:12.640 --> 07:14.080
That'll be you one day, Tom.

07:14.080 --> 07:15.920
- Tom! 
- It took ages, that one...

07:15.920 --> 07:18.800
- Come and look at the model. Anna, Neil, come on. 
- Yeah.

07:22.720 --> 07:26.160
He's not bad at this, is he? Public speaking.

07:26.160 --> 07:28.000
He's worried about his suit.

07:28.000 --> 07:32.760
- Why? 
- He says he looks like he's selling cars.

07:32.760 --> 07:36.160
- Right, yes, I see what you mean! 
- THEY CHUCKLE

07:36.160 --> 07:41.440
Neil, I wanted to ask, could we find a moment to go over my accounts?

07:41.440 --> 07:43.880
I've always left it to Simon,

07:43.880 --> 07:47.280
but I've realised perhaps maybe I should pay more attention.

07:47.280 --> 07:49.920
- I thought you could talk me through it. 
- Sure.

07:50.960 --> 07:52.440
Over dinner maybe.

07:55.080 --> 07:56.600
Absolutely.

07:57.760 --> 07:59.600
And maybe don't mention it to Simon.

08:00.640 --> 08:04.040
- I wouldn't want him thinking that I don't trust him. 
- Of course.

08:06.560 --> 08:08.280
Well, just let me know when.

08:16.640 --> 08:20.840
Simon's right, this is historic.

08:20.840 --> 08:25.600
I gave Karl Lucas a hand job against that wall in 1993.

08:26.680 --> 08:29.200
And now, they're knocking it down!

08:29.200 --> 08:33.000
There was no internet or mobiles in the early '90s.

08:33.000 --> 08:37.440
So, in a town like this, nothing do except each other.

08:38.440 --> 08:39.640
Listen...

08:40.840 --> 08:44.480
Kate changed surgery. We got the paperwork through today.

08:44.480 --> 08:46.360
Makes sense.

08:47.360 --> 08:49.840
- Still need me tomorrow? 
- Yes.

08:49.840 --> 08:52.240
Never been undercover before. It's exciting.

08:52.240 --> 08:54.560
- Thanks. 
- OK.

08:56.200 --> 08:59.640
Mum? If you haven't seen the model, you should.

08:59.640 --> 09:03.040
- Impressed? 
- Mm, I suppose...

09:04.280 --> 09:06.400
- Proud of your dad? 
- A bit, yeah.

09:08.440 --> 09:10.840
- Thank you. 
- What for?

09:12.760 --> 09:14.480
Everything.

09:14.480 --> 09:16.240
It's my pleasure.

09:17.880 --> 09:19.160
Simon!

09:20.440 --> 09:23.480
Sorry, could you just cast your eye over this?

09:38.720 --> 09:40.920
GRAVEL CRUNCHES

09:40.920 --> 09:41.960
I can't do it.

09:44.160 --> 09:47.720
She's going to think I'm selling something, or mental.

09:47.720 --> 09:50.760
You've moved round the corner, just thought you'd say hello.

09:50.760 --> 09:52.680
People don't do that any more.

09:52.680 --> 09:56.480
They might if they're pregnant and want a sense of the community.

09:56.480 --> 10:00.200
Right, I'll just drop all that into the conversation(!)

10:00.200 --> 10:03.360
Say you're tired, put your hand on your tummy, and she'll work it out.

10:03.360 --> 10:05.720
Just...get her to like you.

10:07.040 --> 10:09.680
And then tomorrow, come back, get her talking about Simon,

10:09.680 --> 10:11.800
divorce, plans, anything.

10:11.800 --> 10:16.240
Worst that can happen, she shuts the door in your face.

10:16.240 --> 10:19.000
And if she does, I'll still give you the money.

10:20.960 --> 10:22.840
OK, OK.

10:35.640 --> 10:37.160
MESSAGE ALERT

10:44.960 --> 10:46.880
SHE SIGHS

10:46.880 --> 10:48.160
DOOR OPENS

10:48.160 --> 10:53.400
Hi! Um, my name's Carly, I just moved in round the cor...

10:53.400 --> 10:56.160
Well... and I'm, um...

10:56.160 --> 10:59.120
- I am, too! 
- Are you? Congratulations!

10:59.120 --> 11:00.520
THEY LAUGH

11:00.520 --> 11:01.720
SHE SIGHS

11:01.720 --> 11:04.840
Well, I'm sorry. I'll leave you in peace. It's nice to meet you though.

11:04.840 --> 11:07.320
I will do. Hopefully, I'll see you around or something.

11:07.320 --> 11:08.960
- OK. Bye. 
- DOOR CLOSES

11:15.600 --> 11:17.520
ENGINE STARTS

11:20.120 --> 11:22.040
How did you know?

11:22.040 --> 11:24.560
We moved here when I was pregnant.

11:24.560 --> 11:26.960
First thing I did? Made friends.

11:29.040 --> 11:31.280
At least, that's what I thought they were.

11:34.960 --> 11:36.960
We can stop the current medication,

11:36.960 --> 11:40.080
but in terms of a replacement, it's difficult.

11:40.080 --> 11:42.880
Your pain has proven very resistant to treatment.

11:44.120 --> 11:48.240
From a medical perspective, I would advise we go on as we are.

11:48.240 --> 11:51.280
But that's not to say there aren't any practical steps to make you

11:51.280 --> 11:54.200
more comfortable that you could discuss with the staff here.

11:54.200 --> 11:57.520
- We're having those conversations. 
- Good. Good.

11:57.520 --> 11:58.800
All right.

11:58.800 --> 12:00.360
Thank you for coming.

12:00.360 --> 12:01.600
Thank you.

12:08.040 --> 12:10.920
That's it, then. We just give up.

12:10.920 --> 12:12.360
Mum, no...

12:16.800 --> 12:20.480
If you have a pain in your head like a drill,

12:20.480 --> 12:23.120
all day, and all night,

12:23.120 --> 12:27.080
- how long do you wait? 
- Wait? What do you mean?

12:28.760 --> 12:30.160
Mum, it'll be OK.

12:33.840 --> 12:35.480
It went well today?

12:38.560 --> 12:40.240
Yeah. Really well.

12:40.240 --> 12:42.600
Mm. Proud.

12:45.160 --> 12:46.800
You better get going.

12:46.800 --> 12:48.480
Call us if you need anything.

12:50.160 --> 12:51.320
Love you, Mum.

12:56.360 --> 12:58.400
You understand, don't you?

12:58.400 --> 13:01.920
- Yes. 
- I can't do this forever.

13:01.920 --> 13:03.760
I just can't.

13:05.560 --> 13:06.880
I...

13:06.880 --> 13:08.520
(I can't have this conversation.)

13:10.720 --> 13:12.920
We're not giving up. I promise.

13:12.920 --> 13:15.320
I'll look into options.

13:16.800 --> 13:18.600
See you very soon.

13:32.760 --> 13:35.280
# My baby went away

13:35.280 --> 13:42.240
# He went away across the sea

13:42.240 --> 13:46.720
# It's been two years or so

13:46.720 --> 13:50.320
# Since I saw my baby go

13:50.320 --> 13:54.000
# And then this letter came for me... #

13:54.000 --> 13:56.760
SHE SIGHS

14:05.160 --> 14:06.480
You don't look normal.

14:08.000 --> 14:09.720
You could just say I look nice.

14:09.720 --> 14:12.800
Well, yeah, that's what I mean. It's unusual.

14:14.680 --> 14:17.680
- Thanks, Tom. 
- Long day. Taxi's outside.

14:17.680 --> 14:19.920
- Right. 
- Where are you going again?

14:19.920 --> 14:22.080
Local Medical Committee dinner.

14:22.080 --> 14:23.680
Sounds boring.

14:23.680 --> 14:25.960
Right. OK. And that's a...

14:25.960 --> 14:27.400
What?

14:27.400 --> 14:30.160
- And you wear heels for that, do you? 
- I'm a woman on a night out,

14:30.160 --> 14:33.280
so it's heels or flats, and flats don't go, so...

14:33.280 --> 14:36.520
- What do you want me to wear, trainers? 
- No...just...

14:36.520 --> 14:38.960
- You look really... 
- What?

14:40.120 --> 14:43.560
- It doesn't matter. 
- No, don't stop there. I'm on the way out the house.

14:43.560 --> 14:46.560
- I look really what? 
- I'm knackered. Have we got any crisps?

14:46.560 --> 14:48.680
I've had a tough day, too.

14:48.680 --> 14:50.600
- What time are you home? 
- Late.

14:50.600 --> 14:53.400
I might've gone to bed. Does Tom know what he's having for dinner?

14:53.400 --> 14:55.320
- Yes. 
- And is there anything for...

14:55.320 --> 14:58.240
Leftovers in the fridge. Crisps are in the bottom left cupboard.

14:58.240 --> 15:01.560
- Tom can show you if you get stuck. 
- Right...

15:22.640 --> 15:24.520
SCRAPING

15:41.480 --> 15:43.480
SHE KNOCKS

15:45.320 --> 15:46.520
Hi!

15:46.520 --> 15:47.760
Hi.

15:47.760 --> 15:49.840
I know this is weird, but I...

15:49.840 --> 15:52.080
I ordered a copy of this book,

15:52.080 --> 15:55.520
but I must've ordered it twice cos I got two copies through.

15:55.520 --> 15:58.640
And I thought, well, you're just down the road, you might want it.

16:01.080 --> 16:04.360
- Is Gemma about? 
- She's at a dinner. 
- Oh.

16:04.360 --> 16:06.680
- SHE SNORTS 
- Annoying.

16:06.680 --> 16:08.520
- You all right? 
- Yeah.

16:09.520 --> 16:11.880
- Told her yet? 
- No.

16:11.880 --> 16:13.640
Who's Kate changed doctors to?

16:13.640 --> 16:15.760
We shouldn't talk about all this now.

16:15.760 --> 16:18.080
- Is Tom...? 
- Upstairs.

16:18.080 --> 16:20.840
- Well, are you sure you don't want to send it back? 
- Nah.

16:20.840 --> 16:24.040
- It's...hassle. 
- Well, I can give you the money for it.

16:24.040 --> 16:25.600
No. Go on.

16:27.360 --> 16:29.400
- Thanks. ROS: 
- 'I have come...'

