18:36.800 --> 18:39.360
Despite the fact that the world keeps changing.

18:42.760 --> 18:44.200
People change, as well.

18:47.040 --> 18:49.920
Your work, your house and everything alters,

18:49.920 --> 18:53.000
you're expected to stick with just this one person.

18:55.960 --> 18:58.960
And despite that sounding unlikely, when I met Gemma I thought I could.

18:58.960 --> 19:00.240
I thought, "Actually, yes."

19:03.280 --> 19:05.120
"I'll never need anyone else."

19:12.800 --> 19:13.920
What I didn't realise...

19:16.080 --> 19:18.320
..is that it's possible to feel that

19:18.320 --> 19:20.880
about two different people at the same time.

19:22.640 --> 19:27.000
- You're still in love with Ge... 
- With Gemma. Yeah, of course. Yes!

19:31.280 --> 19:32.600
And Kate.

19:33.600 --> 19:36.440
- Both of them. 
- HE CHUCKLES

19:43.160 --> 19:45.080
The moment I tell Gemma, I lose her.

19:46.240 --> 19:47.560
And I lose my son.

19:48.800 --> 19:50.200
Weekends, evenings...

19:51.560 --> 19:54.160
..and he'll know the truth and he'll hate me.

19:56.000 --> 19:58.560
And that's the only reason you haven't told her?

20:04.200 --> 20:07.320
- She asked you to come tonight, didn't she? 
- No! 
- She suspects.

20:12.520 --> 20:14.160
All right, yes.

20:16.000 --> 20:19.800
Well, she...she doesn't think that you're with someone else.

20:21.160 --> 20:22.800
She's worried that you may be hiding

20:22.800 --> 20:24.680
something with the business, the money.

20:26.720 --> 20:28.200
She thought you might open up.

20:28.200 --> 20:30.800
Why would she think anything's wrong with the money?

20:32.600 --> 20:34.960
She may've noticed how stressed you look.

20:36.320 --> 20:39.480
- I don't look stressed! 
- Stressed is an understatement.

20:39.480 --> 20:42.840
Actually, you're right, you don't look stressed. You look ill.

20:46.440 --> 20:48.800
Is there something wrong with the money?

20:48.800 --> 20:51.520
Well, if there was, I wouldn't tell you now, would I?

20:51.520 --> 20:55.320
- You'd just go straight back to Gemma. 
- I'm not on her side.

20:55.320 --> 20:57.600
I'm stuck in the middle!

20:57.600 --> 20:59.920
I just want what's best!

20:59.920 --> 21:02.720
- Tell me the truth. 
- The truth about the money...

21:02.720 --> 21:04.480
CLATTERING

21:05.600 --> 21:07.880
..is that everything's about this far from fucked.

21:12.040 --> 21:14.680
'Financial matters?'

21:14.680 --> 21:18.200
Yeah. As our accountant, I hoped you could talk me through things.

21:18.200 --> 21:21.240
- Over dinner. 
- Yeah.

21:21.240 --> 21:23.720
What, earnings, tax, that sort of thing?

21:23.720 --> 21:27.040
- That sort of thing exactly. 
- Right...

21:27.040 --> 21:30.720
