Thinks he knows it all. It's ANNOYING.

44:18.360 --> 44:20.280
I keep thinking about last night.

44:21.440 --> 44:24.200
We could meet again, if you want.

44:27.520 --> 44:28.760
White Stone?

44:30.080 --> 44:33.360
- Um, yeah. 
- Will you keep trying to find out who it is?

44:33.360 --> 44:34.640
DOOR OPENS

44:34.640 --> 44:36.800
Hello! Not a bad day out there now.

44:36.800 --> 44:40.120
Got bread and wipes for the kitchen, but there was some...

44:40.120 --> 44:43.480
- Hi, love. 
- Oh! Hi! 
- Hi. 
- I didn't know you were here.

44:43.480 --> 44:45.440
Neil was helping with my accounts.

44:45.440 --> 44:48.960
I think we've got everything sorted, so I should probably head off.

44:48.960 --> 44:51.360
Sorry, I'm in a hurry...

44:51.360 --> 44:54.720
OK, sure. Bye! We'll see you later.

44:56.920 --> 44:58.440
Hey.

44:58.440 --> 45:00.400
Are you all right?

45:01.400 --> 45:03.160
'He'll get nothing.'

45:03.160 --> 45:07.200
Once the divorce starts, it'll all come out,

45:07.200 --> 45:11.040
- him taking your money, forging your signature. 
- Yes.

45:12.320 --> 45:14.840
And the project will collapse probably.

45:14.840 --> 45:16.840
We'll lose it all.

45:16.840 --> 45:19.320
SHE SOBS But I earn enough.

45:19.320 --> 45:22.960
And what he's done only strengthens my case.

45:22.960 --> 45:25.160
Tom and me, we'll be OK.

45:25.160 --> 45:28.360
And I promise we'll always look after you.

45:28.360 --> 45:29.600
What about him?

45:31.240 --> 45:34.560
You probably don't care, I understand that. But...

45:36.000 --> 45:38.440
..you'll look after him?

45:38.440 --> 45:40.360
You won't leave him with nothing?

45:42.160 --> 45:43.760
It'll be fair.

45:46.120 --> 45:47.400
I promise.

45:48.480 --> 45:51.000
VOICEMAIL TONE

45:51.000 --> 45:54.320
Hi, Anwar, I think I've got everything. I want to proceed.

45:54.320 --> 45:55.640
Can you call me back?

46:03.760 --> 46:05.000
Hey. What's the matter?

46:06.760 --> 46:08.680
- Are you OK? 
- I did it.

46:10.600 --> 46:11.960
What? Your boyfriend?

46:11.960 --> 46:14.320
Oh, shit, he followed me.

46:16.600 --> 46:18.520
We can't do this in here.

46:18.520 --> 46:22.520
I told you, I'm only keeping it if you finish it with her.

46:22.520 --> 46:24.360
You said you would!

46:24.360 --> 46:25.800
I want to.

46:25.800 --> 46:27.640
It's not good enough, that.

46:28.680 --> 46:30.720
Anyway...

46:30.720 --> 46:32.440
It's gone now.

46:32.440 --> 46:34.080
It's better.

46:35.440 --> 46:38.640
- It's my body. It's up to me. 
- You know why I couldn't tell her.

46:38.640 --> 46:41.080
Either go and tell her now,

46:41.080 --> 46:42.360
or that is it.

46:43.640 --> 46:45.160
It was my child, too.

46:45.160 --> 46:47.280
Are you going to go and tell her?

46:49.640 --> 46:50.720
No.

46:59.120 --> 47:01.400
You're right, you shouldn't wait any more.

47:07.680 --> 47:09.680
DOOR CLOSES

47:11.040 --> 47:13.000
'He left. She waited.'

47:13.000 --> 47:14.160
He didn't come back.

47:15.600 --> 47:18.640
And do you think it's really over?

47:18.640 --> 47:21.440
She had it done without telling him.

47:21.440 --> 47:23.640
He looked like he'd never forget that.

47:25.960 --> 47:28.960
Maybe it doesn't matter, but in the end,

47:28.960 --> 47:30.720
he was the one that finished it.

47:30.720 --> 47:32.440
He told her not to wait.

47:36.040 --> 47:37.720
That doesn't change anything.

47:50.960 --> 47:53.800
TOM LAUGHS

48:03.760 --> 48:06.760
TOM GIGGLES

48:14.040 --> 48:15.880
LAUGHTER FROM TV

48:15.880 --> 48:19.280
SHE PIERCES LOUDLY

48:23.400 --> 48:25.800
Everything all right?

48:25.800 --> 48:27.560
Just about.

48:30.600 --> 48:33.400
- Hard at the moment, isn't it? 
- LAUGHTER FROM TV NEARBY

48:42.960 --> 48:45.120
We were watching a thing.

48:45.120 --> 48:47.000
It's...it's funny.

48:48.720 --> 48:50.360
I'll be over in a minute.

49:22.000 --> 49:23.960
PHONE RINGS

49:33.280 --> 49:34.440
Hello?

49:36.560 --> 49:37.920
Yes?

49:43.520 --> 49:45.800
Yeah, yeah. I'll be there as soon as I can.

50:03.360 --> 50:05.480
I'm so sorry.

50:05.480 --> 50:08.880
- Have the police spoken to you? 
- No. 
- They just said to wait.

50:10.240 --> 50:13.400
She took an overdose of sleeping pills.

50:15.080 --> 50:16.720
Left a short note.

50:16.720 --> 50:20.280
It says that the pain had got too much,

50:20.280 --> 50:22.840
and she couldn't carry on.

50:22.840 --> 50:25.680
- But, then, why didn't she tell us. 
- She did. 
- Yes, but...

50:25.680 --> 50:26.960
We knew she was suffering,

50:26.960 --> 50:29.520
there just wasn't anything that we could do to help.

50:39.520 --> 50:40.960
How did she get the pills?

50:42.120 --> 50:44.840
In the note, she talks about storing them up for a long time,

50:44.840 --> 50:47.600
pretending to take them and saving them.

50:49.920 --> 50:52.400
This sort of thing, it does happen.

50:54.800 --> 50:57.520
You never gave her..?

50:57.520 --> 50:58.920
I'm sorry?

50:58.920 --> 51:01.160
Something they asked me.

51:01.160 --> 51:03.160
- Whether you might. 
- I wouldn't.

51:08.360 --> 51:09.840
Oh, Simon.

51:29.720 --> 51:32.080
- What's happened? 
- Come and sit down.

51:39.920 --> 51:43.600
Mate, you know Granny was, um, very ill.

51:43.600 --> 51:44.840
She was hurting all the time.

51:44.840 --> 51:46.560
Yeah, yes.

51:46.560 --> 51:51.120
Well, I'm afraid, last night, she passed away.

51:51.120 --> 51:52.680
She died in her sleep.

51:58.120 --> 52:01.200
- She's...she's... 
- It was peaceful. She's not in pain any more.

52:02.560 --> 52:05.880
TOM SOBS

52:08.840 --> 52:11.600
- TEARFULLY: 
- It's really sad. I'm sorry.

52:21.400 --> 52:23.600
Oh, Tom...

52:33.680 --> 52:35.080
I thought it might help.

52:36.720 --> 52:38.600
Maybe you could give it a try?

52:39.720 --> 52:41.760
You think it's silly, hey?

52:47.760 --> 52:50.120
I'm just going to go and see your dad.

53:12.680 --> 53:16.880
When my mum and dad died, the woman who looked after me, Mary,

53:16.880 --> 53:19.440
she gave me a notebook to write down how I felt.

53:20.760 --> 53:21.800
Stupid.

53:26.840 --> 53:29.000
Not at all.

53:38.680 --> 53:40.840
PHONE BUZZES

53:40.840 --> 53:42.040
Sorry.

53:50.840 --> 53:53.240
Hi. Anwar. Yeah...

53:54.560 --> 53:55.880
No.

54:00.080 --> 54:01.920
I've changed my mind.

54:03.480 --> 54:04.960
We're all right.

54:06.560 --> 54:08.120
We're going to try again.

54:27.240 --> 54:29.360
HE SOBS LOUDLY

54:33.080 --> 54:36.440
HE CRIES

55:10.960 --> 55:12.840
"What's typhoid"?

55:12.840 --> 55:16.480
How can you simply take him back?

55:16.480 --> 55:20.280
Because we have a child together. A life together.

55:20.280 --> 55:21.800
14 years under our belt,

55:21.800 --> 55:24.360
so if there's any way of keeping all of that, I have to try.

55:24.360 --> 55:27.800
And you honestly think that he's never going to see her again?

55:30.480 --> 55:32.440
TEXT ALERT

55:34.480 --> 55:36.960
You think I'm lying? You still don't trust me?

